      <div class="requirement-block">
        <h3>1. Personal therapist requirement for Dr. Phillip Collier</h3>
        <p>The recommendation says that after sixteen family therapy sessions are completed, Father continues twice-monthly individual therapy with Dr. Phillip Collier for twelve sessions. The stated purpose is support with parenting and co-parenting, plus unresolved issues in the marriage to Mother.</p>
        <ul class="checklist" data-checklist="individual-therapy">
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="setup"> Ask Dr. Collier for a written attendance and compliance letter for current therapy.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="setup"> Keep the letter limited to attendance, active participation, treatment status, and scheduling, without privileged clinical detail.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="post16"> After sixteen family therapy sessions, schedule twelve twice-monthly individual therapy sessions with Dr. Collier.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="post16"> Confirm Dr. Collier can address parenting, co-parenting, and unresolved marriage issues as stated in the recommendation.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="post16"> Have Dr. Collier contact the evaluator at 209-425-2729 before the third session to discuss the referral reason, if counsel approves that contact.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="post16"> File or send proof of attendance to Mother’s attorney after the first, sixth, and twelfth sessions.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="post16"> Confirm whether Dr. Collier and the co-parenting facilitator may communicate with each other about progress in both therapies.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="proof"> Save all letters, session confirmations, and proof transmissions as PDFs.</label></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="requirement-block">
        <h3>2. Janz family therapy setup</h3>
        <p>The recommendation calls for both parties and the minors to participate in twenty-four sessions of family therapy with a licensed mental health professional experienced with families in high-conflict divorces. Mother participates in half of the sessions. The first sixteen sessions are weekly, and the remaining eight sessions are twice monthly.</p>
        <ul class="checklist" data-checklist="family-therapy">
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="setup"> Send the Janz follow-up draft after approval.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="setup"> Confirm what documents are pending in the Janz portal and who must complete each one.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="setup"> Confirm Brooke’s required consent, intake paperwork, attendance, and support obligations before scheduling.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="setup"> Confirm Janz can provide family therapy involving both parents and the children together as required or clinically directed.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="setup"> Ask whether Janz needs a copy of the custody recommendation or order before scheduling.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="family"> Complete the first four sessions with both parents plus Harrison and Waylon, unless counsel or the therapist confirms a different court-approved structure.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="family"> Complete the next alternating sessions for Dylan and the whole-minor group as directed by the family therapist and recommendation.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="family"> Confirm the family therapist has a copy of the evaluation report and treats it as confidential.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="family"> File written proof of attendance for the first, sixth, twelfth, sixteenth, and twenty-fourth family therapy sessions.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="proof"> Save all Janz replies, appointment confirmations, attendance letters, cancellation notices, and refusal documentation as PDFs.</label></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="requirement-block">
        <h3>3. Anger management course in Fresno</h3>
        <p>The recommendation says Father participates in ten once-weekly in-person anger-management classes. Written proof of attendance must be filed with the Court and copied to Mother after the first, fourth, and tenth classes.</p>
        <ul class="checklist" data-checklist="anger-management">
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="setup"> Call providers and confirm live, in-person Fresno-area availability.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="setup"> Confirm the program is suitable for court-related anger-management compliance.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="anger"> Enroll in a ten-session once-weekly in-person anger-management class.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="anger"> Attend the first class and get written proof.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="anger"> File first-class proof with the Court and copy Mother.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="anger"> Attend the fourth class and get written proof.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="anger"> File fourth-class proof with the Court and copy Mother.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="anger"> Complete the tenth class and get written proof or certificate.</label></li>
          <li><label><input type="checkbox" data-stage="anger"> File tenth-class proof with the Court and copy Mother.</label></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="requirement-block">
        <h3>4. Step-up visitation proof gates</h3>
        <p>These are tracking milestones only. Counsel should confirm exact trigger language before using this page to claim compliance.</p>
        <ul class="checklist" data-checklist="step-up">
